{
  "stem": "15174.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "My mother was left alone without any support with a little child, but this little child developed diphtheria, which in those days was a-- was a-- could be a fatal disease.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "There were no antibiotics.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "I guess I was treated with an antiserum.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And I-- I obviously survived.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "But it was just another terrible business in this terrible sequence of events.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "I told you that my uncle Alter had already emigrated to the United States in September of 1938.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "It became pretty clear to most Jews living in Germany that, you know, it was an untenable situation, that you just couldn't stay there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "And so a lot of people [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] looked for countries to go to.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "We had some relatives in the United States.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "And besides, the United States had a reputation of-- of-- of being a good place to live in, and so a lot of people applied for a visa to the United States, including my father.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "I don't know exactly when he applied.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "It was probably early 1935 or something like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "Now, you know, the United States used to allow immigrants to come in freely.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "I mean, there were no immigration laws.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "The only thing was that if you were sick or you had certain diseases, you were not allowed in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "You were sent back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "But that-- that encompassed about maybe 1% of the people who actually arrived on the shores of the United States.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 87,
      "text": "But in 1924, an immigration bill was passed, which severely limited the number of immigrants who come in-- who could come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 88,
      "text": "It was based on a quota system.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
